LogFile.FinalText: Some people say that men and women speak different languages. If the man in a relationship says that he does not want to talk about his problems, the woman will typically feel that she is being held out of his world. If the woman tells him that she does not want to talk about her problems, most men believe that she has no need to talk about them. These misunderstandings often result in arguments. When they are having a fight, men and women also react in different ways. Recent research shows that many women cry when they get angry. This will cause the man to get scared and run away, and he may feel helpless. As opposed to the crying women, men show their anger by using strong words. Despite these different reactions, most men and women live peacefully together, and we probably cannot live without each other.
